    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi there,\n\nI noticed that `test_command_error` in `test/test_vim.py` fails when running against Neovim 0.12.0+. \n\nThe test asserts the exact error message string \"Cursor position outside buffer\", but this message was changed to \"Invalid cursor line: out of range\" in Neovim 0.12.0 (specifically in neovim commit [680d25e](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/680d25e5b3c1efba13bd8f5c0bd6bb5ab431361f)).\n\nNot sure what the right thing to do is, but I guess the test should probably be a bit less fragile.\n\nThe only reason I noticed was because i was attempting to update the neovim package to 0.12.1 in the guix package manager, which runs a packages test suite as part of its build by default...",
